                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  209-210</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Written in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1758"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="175806" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">mid-June 1758</date>
                     </extref> at the request of 
							<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Wharton, Thomas, 1717-1794"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname role="trc" normal="Wharton, Thomas,          1717-1794">Thomas Wharton</persname>
                     </extref> to commemorate his eldest 
							son	<persname normal="Wharton, Robert, 1753-1758">Robin</persname> who
							died in <date normal="175804" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">April 1758</date>.
							First published in <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#GoE_1884"
                             linktype="simple"> Gosse (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Works</title> (1884), vol. I,  126</bibref>, from the
							<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/findingaid/mss.0052.xml">transcript</extref> made by <extref href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander_Dyce"
                             show="new"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname role="trc" normal="Dyce, Alexander, 1798-1869">Alexander	Dyce</persname>
                     </extref>.
						</p>
